a.xlink:title: Role of a party in an activity.
Specifies roles played by a party that are linked to the handling of assets but not related to a specific process.
Specifies roles played by a party that are linked to the handling of securities but not related to a specific process.
Organisation used as the safekeeping place for the securities.
Type of entity that plays a specific role in a specific context.

Person to be contacted in a given organisation. In the corporate action domain (including meeting notifications) , it is the contact person at the party organising the meeting, at the issuer or at an intermediary.
Calculation of the exposure amount that one party has vis-a-vis one counterparty or a central system, based on its credit risk.
Posting to an account that results in an increase or decrease to a balance.
Tangible items of value to a business.
Account to or from which a securities entry is made.
Account to or from which a cash entry is made.
Financial instruments representing a sum of rights of the investor vis-a-vis the issuer.

Net position of a segregated holding, in a single security, within the overall position held in a securities account. A securities balance is calculated from the sum of securities' receipts minus the sum of securities' deliveries.
Settlement of the securities in a securities transaction, that is, the instruction to deliver or receive securities, involving the payment of an amount of money or not.
